Interface FinalizableQueryBuilder

    public interface FinalizableQueryBuilder

    • Method Detail

      • toQuery

        ChronoDBQuery toQuery()
        Returns the previously built query, in a stand-alone format.

        The returned query is independent of the transaction and consequently independent of the transaction timestamp. This method should be used when the result of a query at different timestamps is of interest. The resulting query can be executed via ChronoDBTransaction.find(ChronoDBQuery).

        Returns:
        The built query. Never null.

      • count

        long count()
        Executes the previously built query, returning the count of matching elements.

        Usage example: 

         long resultCount = tx.find().where("name").contains("hello").count();
        Returns:
        The count of keys matching the query. Never negative.

      • and

        QueryBuilder and()
        Extends the query by adding a logical "and" operator.
        Returns:
        The next builder for method chaining. Never null.

      • or

        QueryBuilder or()
        Extends the query by adding a logical "or" operator.
        Returns:
        The next builder for method chaining. Never null.
